10 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
11 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
12 Article – Commercial Law
13 13–301.
14 Unfair, abusive, or deceptive trade practices include any:
15 (14) Violation of a provision of:
16 (xlvii) Title 14, Subtitle 50 of this article; [or]
17 (xlviii) Section 13–411.1(c)(2) of the Transportation Article; or
18 (XLIX) TITLE 9, SUBTITLE 1F OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
19 ARTICLE; OR
20 Article – State Government
21 SUBTITLE 1F. ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING.
22 9–1F–01.
23 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
24 INDICATED.
25 (B) “COMMISSION” MEANS THE STATE LOTTERY AND GAMING CONTROL
26 COMMISSION.
27 (C) “DIVISION” MEANS THE DIVISION OF CONSUMER PROTECTION OF THE
28 OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL.
29 (D) “FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER” MEANS ANY PERSON THAT
30 FACILITATES OR PARTICIPATES IN ANY FINANCIAL TRANSACTION BETWEEN AN

HOUSE BILL 1226 3
1 ONLINE GAMBLING PLAYER AND AN ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR, INCLUDING A
2 PAYMENT PROCESSOR, CREDIT CARD ISSUER, FINANCIAL INSTITUTION, MONEY
3 TRANSMITTING BUSINESS, OR PAYMENT NETWORK UTILIZED TO EFFECT A CREDIT
4 CARD TRANSACTION, A DEBIT CARD TRANSACTION, AN ELECTRONIC FUND
5 TRANSFER OR A MONEY TRANSMITTING SERVICE, OR ANY OTHER PARTICIPANT IN A
6 DESIGNATED PAYMENT SYSTEM.
7 (E) “ILLEGAL” MEANS NOT EXPRESSLY AUTHORIZED BY APPLICABLE LAW.
8 (F) “ONLINE GAMBLING” MEANS THE BUSINESS OF OFFERING OR
9 ACCEPTING WAGERS, THROUGH AN ONLINE GAMING SYSTEM ON A COMPUTER,
10 MOBILE DEVICE, TABLET, OR ANY OTHER INTERACTIVE DEVICE, ON ANY GAME,
11 CONTEST, LOTTERY, PROMOTION, OR CONTRIVANCE THEREOF, INCLUDING TABLE
12 GAMES, SLOT MACHINES, VIDEO POKER, SWEEPSTAKES GAMES, GAMES OF CHANCE,
13 AND ANY OTHER GAME TYPICALLY OFFERED IN A CASINO.
14 (G) (1) “ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR” MEANS A PERSON WHO OWNS,
15 MAINTAINS, OR OPERATES AN INTERNET WEBSITE THAT IS USED FOR ILLEGAL
16 ONLINE GAMBLING.
17 (2) “ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR” DOES NOT INCLUDE A PERSON
18 LICENSED TO CONDUCT ONLINE SPORTS WAGERING OR FANTASY COMPETITIONS
19 UNDER SUBTITLES 1D AND 1E OF THIS TITLE.
20 (H) “PLATFORM PROVIDER” MEANS ANY PERSON THAT:
21 (1) STORES OR HOSTS CONTENT, FILES, DATA, AND OTHER
22 INFORMATION ON A WEB SERVER; AND
23 (2) MAKES THE CONTENT, FILES, DATA, OR OTHER INFORMATION
24 ACCESSIBLE ON AN INTERNET WEBSITE VIA A COMPUTER, MOBILE DEVICE, TABLET,
25 OR OTHER INTERACTIVE DEVICE.
26 (I) “SWEEPSTAKES GAMES” MEANS A GAME, CONTEST, OR PROMOTION
27 THAT:
28 (1) UTILIZES A DUAL–CURRENCY SYSTEM OF PAYMENT ALLOWING
29 THE PLAYER TO EXCHANGE THE CURRENCY FOR ANY PRIZE, AWARD, CASH OR CASH
30 EQUIVALENTS, OR CHANCE TO WIN ANY PRIZE, AWARD, CASH OR CASH
31 EQUIVALENTS; AND
32 (2) SIMULATES ANY FORM OF GAMBLING, INCLUDING:

4 HOUSE BILL 1226
1 (I) CASINO–STYLE GAMES, INCLUDING SLOT MACHINES, VIDEO
2 POKER, AND TABLE GAMES SUCH AS BLACKJACK, ROULETTE, CRAPS, AND POKER;
3 (II) LOTTERY GAMES INCLUDING DRAW GAMES, INSTANT WIN
4 GAMES, KENO, AND BINGO; AND
5 (III) SPORTS WAGERING.
6 (J) “WAGER” MEANS THE PROVISION OF CONSIDERATION, INCLUDING
7 MONEY OR ANYTHING OF VALUE, IN EXCHANGE FOR THE OPPORTUNITY TO PLAY ANY
8 GAME, CONTEST, LOTTERY, OR CONTRIVANCE AND RECEIVE MONEY OR SOMETHING
9 OF VALUE IN THE EVENT OF A CERTAIN OUTCOME, WHICH OUTCOME IS DETERMINED
10 BY SKILL, CHANCE, OR ELEMENTS OF SKILL AND CHANCE.
11 9–1F–02.
12 THIS SUBTITLE DOES NOT APPLY TO A PERSON LICENSED TO OFFER ONLINE
13 SPORTS WAGERING OR FANTASY COMPETITIONS UNDER SUBTITLES 1D AND 1E OF
14 THIS TITLE.
15 9–1F–03.
16 A PERSON MAY NOT KNOWINGLY:
17 (1) OPERATE, OFFER, CONDUCT, ENGAGE IN, OR PROMOTE ILLEGAL
18 ONLINE GAMBLING IN THE STATE; OR
19 (2) KNOWINGLY SUPPORT, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, THE
20 OPERATION, CONDUCT, OR PROMOTION OF ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING IN THE
21 STATE.
22 9–1F–04.
23 (A) (1) THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL, ACTING THROUGH
24 THE DIVISION, OR A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY MAY ISSUE A WRITTEN CEASE AND
25 DESIST ORDER TO ANY PERSON THAT VIOLATES § 9–1F–03(1) OF THIS SUBTITLE.
26 (2) A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL:
27 (I) SPECIFY THE ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING ACTIVITY;
28 (II) STATE THAT THE PERSON HAS 10 DAYS AFTER THE DATE ON
29 WHICH THE ORDER IS RECEIVED TO BLOCK THE ABILITY OF INDIVIDUALS

HOUSE BILL 1226 5
1 PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE STATE TO ACCESS THE ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING
2 ACTIVITY; AND
3 (III) STATE THAT FAILURE TO BLOCK ACCESS TO THE ILLEGAL
4 ONLINE GAMBLING ACTIVITY WITHIN 10 DAYS MAY RESULT IN IMPRISONMENT OR A
5 FINE OR BOTH, AS PROVIDED UNDER § 9–1F–06(A)(1) OF THIS SUBTITLE.
6 (B) (1) A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY WHO IS NOT THE ATTORNEY
7 GENERAL WHO ISSUES A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
8 SECTION SHALL FORWARD A COPY OF THE ORDER TO THE ATTORNEY GENERAL.
9 (2) THE ATTORNEY GENERAL SHALL MAINTAIN:
10 (I) A DEPOSITORY TO COLLECT, MAINTAIN, AND RETAIN EACH
11 CEASE AND DESIST ORDER ISSUED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION; AND
12 (II) A LIST, PUBLICLY AVAILABLE ON THE OFFICE OF THE
13 ATTORNEY GENERAL’S INTERNET WEBSITE, THAT IDENTIFIES THE NAME OF EACH
14 ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR AND THE ASSOCIATED ONLINE GAMBLING INTERNET
15 WEBSITE URL ADDRESS THAT HAS BEEN ISSUED A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER.
16 (3) THE FAILURE OF A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY OR THE ATTORNEY
17 GENERAL TO COMPLY WITH THIS SUBSECTION IS NOT A DEFENSE TO ANY ACTION
18 COMMENCED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
19 (C) (1) A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER ISSUED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF
20 THIS SECTION SHALL BE SERVED:
21 (I) IN COMPLIANCE WITH MARYLAND RULES 2–121 AND 2–124;
22 OR
23 (II) BY PUBLICATION IN COMPLIANCE WITH MARYLAND RULE
24 2–122(A)(2).
25 (2) THE ATTORNEY GENERAL IS NOT REQUIRED TO MAKE
26 REASONABLE EFFORTS TO LOCATE THE ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR BEFORE
27 SERVING THE CEASE AND DESIST ORDER BY PUBLICATION.
28 (D) A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER SERVED UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS
29 SECTION:
30 (1) IS ADMISSIBLE IN ANY PROCEEDING UNDER THIS SUBTITLE; AND

6 HOUSE BILL 1226
1 (2) CONSTITUTES PRIMA FACIE EVIDENCE THAT THE PERSON HAS
2 KNOWLEDGE THAT ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING WAS OCCURRING ON THE ONLINE
3 GAMBLING OPERATOR’S INTERNET WEBSITE.
4 (E) A PERSON OUTSIDE THE STATE WHO OWNS, MAINTAINS, OR OPERATES
5 AN INTERNET WEBSITE THAT TRANSMITS INFORMATION THROUGH OR WITH A
6 PLATFORM PROVIDER AND WHO KNOWS OR SHOULD HAVE KNOWN THAT THE
7 INFORMATION IS BROADCAST WITHIN THE STATE SUBMITS TO THE JURISDICTION
8 OF STATE COURTS FOR ENFORCEMENT UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
9 (F) BEFORE ISSUING A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER UNDER SUBSECTION (A)
10 OF THIS SECTION, THE ATTORNEY GENERAL MAY PROVIDE REASONABLE NOTICE TO
11 THE COMMISSION TO ALLOW THE COMMISSION TO DETERMINE WHETHER IT WILL
12 JOIN THE ORDER.
13 9–1F–05.
14 WHENEVER THE ATTORNEY GENERAL, ACTING THROUGH THE DIVISION, OR
15 A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY HAS REASON TO BELIEVE THAT A PERSON IS VIOLATING
16 § 9–1F–03 OF THIS SUBTITLE OR TAKING ANY OTHER ACTION IN VIOLATION OF THIS
17 SUBTITLE, THE ATTORNEY GENERAL OR A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY MAY BRING AN
18 ACTION IN THE NAME OF THE STATE TO RESTRAIN BY TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT
19 INJUNCTION THE CONDUCT GIVING RISE TO THE VIOLATION.
20 9–1F–06.
21 (A) (1) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES § 9–1F–03(1) OF THIS SUBTITLE IS
22 GUILTY OF A MISDEMEANOR AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO:
23 (I) FOR A FIRST VIOLATION, IMPRISONMENT NOT EXCEEDING 3
24 YEARS OR A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $50,000 OR BOTH; AND
25 (II) FOR EACH SUBSEQUENT VIOLATION, IMPRISONMENT NOT
26 EXCEEDING 3 YEARS OR A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $100,000 OR BOTH.
27 (2) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES § 9–1F–03(2) OF THIS SUBTITLE IS
28 SUBJECT TO:
29 (I) FOR A FIRST VIOLATION, A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $25,000;
30 AND
31 (II) FOR EACH SUBSEQUENT VIOLATION, A FINE NOT
32 EXCEEDING $50,000.

HOUSE BILL 1226 7
1 (B) FOR PURPOSES OF THIS SECTION:
2 (1) EACH ONLINE GAMBLING WAGER OFFERED OR ACCEPTED BY A
3 PERSON CONSTITUTES A SEPARATE VIOLATION; AND
4 (2) EACH INDIVIDUAL PROMOTION OF ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING IN
5 THE STATE CONSTITUTES A SEPARATE VIOLATION.
6 (C) A COURT SHALL ORDER THE FORFEITURE OF ANY PROFITS, GAINS,
7 GROSS RECEIPTS, OR OTHER BENEFITS EARNED BY A PERSON IN CONNECTION WITH
8 A VIOLATION OF THIS SUBTITLE.
9 (D) THE COMMISSION SHALL REVOKE A GAMING LICENSE ISSUED UNDER
10 THIS TITLE HELD BY A PERSON FOUND TO HAVE VIOLATED § 9–1F–03 OF THIS
11 SUBTITLE, AND THE PERSON IS INELIGIBLE IN THE FUTURE TO HOLD A GAMING
12 LICENSE ISSUED BY THE COMMISSION.
13 9–1F–07.
14 (A) A FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER MAY NOT KNOWINGLY ACCEPT
15 OR PROCESS ANY FINANCIAL TRANSACTION IN CONNECTION WITH THE
16 PARTICIPATION OF A PERSON IN ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING.
17 (B) A FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER SHALL BE DEEMED TO HAVE
18 CONSTRUCTIVE KNOWLEDGE THAT ALL PERSONS AND INTERNET WEBSITE URLS
19 IDENTIFIED BY THE ATTORNEY GENERAL IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 9–1F–04 OF THIS
20 SUBTITLE ARE ENGAGED IN ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING.
21 9–1F–08.
22 (A) (1) A PLATFORM PROVIDER MAY NOT RECEIVE OR TRANSMIT
23 THROUGH ITS SERVICE ANY EXCHANGE OF INFORMATION THAT IT REASONABLY
24 BELIEVES IS OR WILL BE SENT IN CONNECTION WITH THE PARTICIPATION OF A
25 PERSON IN ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING.
26 (2) A PLATFORM PROVIDER IS DEEMED TO HAVE CONSTRUCTIVE
27 KNOWLEDGE THAT ALL PERSONS AND WEBSITE URLS IDENTIFIED BY THE
28 ATTORNEY GENERAL IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 9–1F–04 OF THIS SUBTITLE ARE
29 ENGAGED IN ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING.
30 (B) BEFORE HOSTING, FACILITATING, OR TRANSMITTING ANY ONLINE
31 GAMBLING ADVERTISEMENT ON A WEBSITE, A PLATFORM PROVIDER SHALL:

8 HOUSE BILL 1226
1 (1) OBTAIN A CERTIFIED COPY OF THE ONLINE GAMBLING
2 OPERATOR’S LICENSE OR PERMIT TO OFFER ONLINE GAMBLING IN THE STATE; OR
3 (2) OBTAIN WRITTEN CONFIRMATION FROM THE COMMISSION THAT
4 THE OPERATOR IS LICENSED OR PERMITTED TO OFFER ONLINE GAMBLING IN THE
5 STATE.
6 9–1F–09.
7 (A) (1) A PLATFORM PROVIDER MAY, ON ITS OWN INITIATIVE, BLOCK THE
8 RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION THROUGH ITS SERVICE ANY EXCHANGE OF
9 INFORMATION THAT IT REASONABLY BELIEVES IS OR WILL BE SENT IN VIOLATION
10 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
11 (2) A PLATFORM PROVIDER MAY NOT BE HELD LIABLE IN TORT TO
12 ANY PERSON FOR BLOCKING THE RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION OF INFORMATION
13 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
14 (3) (I) THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL, ACTING
15 THROUGH THE DIVISION, OR A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY MAY ISSUE A WRITTEN
16 CEASE AND DESIST ORDER TO A PLATFORM PROVIDER DIRECTING THAT IT BLOCK
17 THE RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION THROUGH ITS SERVICE OF ANY EXCHANGE OF
18 INFORMATION IN VIOLATION OF THIS SUBTITLE AND TAKE DOWN OR DISABLE ANY
19 INTERNET WEBSITE CONDUCTING OR OFFERING ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING TO
20 PERSONS PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE STATE.
21 (II) THE CEASE AND DESIST ORDER SHALL:
22 1. IDENTIFY THE ONLINE GAMBLING INTERNET
23 WEBSITE URL THAT THE PLATFORM PROVIDER MUST DISABLE AND FOR WHICH IT
24 MUST BLOCK THE RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION OF ANY EXCHANGE OF INFORMATION
25 THROUGH ITS SERVICE;
26 2. STATE THAT THE PLATFORM PROVIDER HAS 30 DAYS
27 AFTER THE DATE ON WHICH THE ORDER IS RECEIVED TO DISABLE THE ONLINE
28 GAMBLING WEBSITE FROM ACCESS BY INDIVIDUALS PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE
29 STATE AND BLOCK THE RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION OF INFORMATION THROUGH ITS
30 SERVICE AS REQUIRED IN THE ORDER; AND
31 3. STATE THAT FAILURE TO DISABLE THE ONLINE
32 GAMBLING INTERNET WEBSITE FROM ACCESS BY PERSONS PHYSICALLY LOCATED
33 IN THE STATE AND BLOCK THE RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION OF INFORMATION

HOUSE BILL 1226 9
1 THROUGH ITS SERVICE WITHIN 30 DAYS AFTER RECEIVING THE ORDER MAY RESULT
2 IN A FINE UNDER § 9–1F–06(A)(2) OF THIS SUBTITLE FOR EACH DAY THAT THE
3 ONLINE GAMBLING INTERNET WEBSITE URL IS NOT DISABLED TO PERSONS
4 PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE STATE AND FOR EACH RECEIPT OR TRANSMISSION OF
5 INFORMATION THROUGH ITS SERVICE AS REQUIRED IN THE ORDER.
6 (III) A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER ISSUED UNDER THIS
7 PARAGRAPH MAY BE SERVED ON A PLATFORM PROVIDER BY REGISTERED MAIL OR
8 FIRST–CLASS MAIL AT ANY ADDRESS REGISTERED WITH THE STATE FOR THE
9 PLATFORM PROVIDER OR AT WHICH THE PLATFORM PROVIDER CONDUCTS
10 BUSINESS.
11 (IV) A PLATFORM PROVIDER SHALL TIMELY COMPLY WITH A
12 CEASE AND DESIST ORDER SERVED IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS PARAGRAPH.
13 (V) A CEASE AND DESIST ORDER SERVED UNDER THIS
14 PARAGRAPH:
15 1. IS ADMISSIBLE IN ANY PROCEEDING UNDER THIS
16 SUBTITLE; AND
17 2. CONSTITUTES PRIMA FACIE EVIDENCE THAT A
18 PLATFORM PROVIDER HAD KNOWLEDGE THAT ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING WAS
19 OCCURRING ON THE ONLINE GAMBLING INTERNET WEBSITE URL IDENTIFIED IN
20 THE ORDER.
21 (VI) A PLATFORM PROVIDER WHOSE PRINCIPAL PLACE OF
