23 INFORMATION OVER THE INTERNET TO OR FROM PERSONS PHYSICALLY LOCATED
24 IN THE STATE SUBMITS TO THE JURISDICTION OF STATE COURTS FOR
25 ENFORCEMENT UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
26 (B) (1) A FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER MAY, ON ITS OWN
27 INITIATIVE, BLOCK, PROHIBIT, PREVENT, OR OTHERWISE REFUSE TO HONOR ANY
28 FINANCIAL TRANSACTION THAT IT REASONABLY BELIEVES IS OR WILL BE IN
29 VIOLATION OF § 9–1F–07 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
30 (2) A FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER MAY NOT BE HELD LIABLE
31 IN TORT TO ANY PERSON FOR TAKING THE ACTIONS AUTHORIZED UNDER
32 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
33 (C) (1) THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL, ACTING THROUGH
34 THE DIVISION, OR A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY MAY ISSUE A WRITTEN CEASE AND

