6 9–1F–10.
7 (A) (1) IN ADDITION TO ANY OTHER REMEDY UNDER CURRENT LAW, ON
8 APPLICATION BY THE ATTORNEY GENERAL OR A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY AND
9 REGARDLESS OF WHETHER PROCEEDINGS HAVE BEEN INITIATED UNDER THIS
10 SUBTITLE, A COURT MAY ISSUE ANY RELIEF THAT IT DEEMS APPROPRIATE TO
11 PREVENT AND RESTRAIN ACTIVITIES PROHIBITED BY THIS SUBTITLE.
12 (2) THE RELIEF MAY INCLUDE A TEMPORARY RESTRAINING ORDER, A
13 PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION, OR AN INJUNCTION AGAINST ANY PERSON TO PREVENT
14 OR RESTRAIN ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING AND ANY RELATED TRANSACTIONS OR
15 ACTIVITIES, INCLUDING THE REMOVAL OF ANY ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING
16 INTERNET WEBSITE, THE FREEZING OF BANK OR CREDIT ACCOUNTS ASSOCIATED
17 WITH THE INTERNET WEBSITE OR THE ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING ACTIVITY, AND
18 THE REMOVAL OF A PERSON’S ACCESS TO SUCH INTERNET WEBSITES OR ACCOUNTS
19 BY A PERSON WHO PARTICIPATES IN THE ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING ACTIVITY.
20 (3) IN AN ACTION SEEKING INJUNCTIVE RELIEF, A VIOLATION OF
21 THIS SUBTITLE IS CONCLUSIVELY DETERMINED TO BE AN IRREPARABLE HARM.
22 (B) (1) IN ADDITION TO THE REMEDIES AVAILABLE UNDER SUBSECTION
23 (A) OF THIS SECTION, THE ATTORNEY GENERAL OR A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY MAY
24 SEEK AN EX PARTE INJUNCTION TO:
25 (I) COMPEL A PLATFORM PROVIDER TO REMOVE OR DISABLE
26 ACCESS TO AN INTERNET WEBSITE VIOLATING THIS SUBTITLE OR A HYPERTEXT
27 LINK TO A WEBSITE VIOLATING THIS SUBTITLE;
28 (II) ENJOIN A FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER FROM
29 PROCESSING TRANSACTIONS FOR THE ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR; AND
30 (III) COMPEL A PERSON TO DISCONTINUE SUPPORTING ILLEGAL
31 ONLINE GAMBLING IN THE STATE.

12 HOUSE BILL 1226
1 (2) A HEARING ON THE EX PARTE INJUNCTION MUST BE HELD WITHIN
2 30 DAYS AFTER IT IS FILED, AND AFTER THE HEARING THE COURT MAY CONVERT
3 THE INJUNCTION TO A PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION.
4 (C) (1) THE RELIEF GRANTED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OR (B) OF THIS
5 SECTION AGAINST A PLATFORM PROVIDER THAT IS NOT OTHERWISE ENGAGED IN
6 ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING SHALL:
7 (I) BE LIMITED TO THE REMOVAL OF OR DISABLING OF ACCESS
8 TO THE INTERNET WEBSITE VIOLATING THIS SUBTITLE, OR A HYPERTEXT LINK TO
9 AN INTERNET WEBSITE VIOLATING THIS SUBTITLE, THAT IS STORED ON A
10 COMPUTER SERVER THAT THE PLATFORM PROVIDER CONTROLS OR OPERATES;
11 (II) SPECIFY THE INTERNET WEBSITE TO WHICH IT APPLIES;
12 AND
13 (III) SPECIFY THE INTERNET WEBSITE OR HYPERTEXT LINK TO
14 BE REMOVED OR ACCESS TO WHICH IS TO BE DISABLED.
15 (2) A VIOLATION OF AN ORDER ENTERED AGAINST A PLATFORM
16 PROVIDER IS PUNISHABLE BY A FINE OF $50,000 FOR A FIRST VIOLATION AND
17 $100,000 FOR EACH SUBSEQUENT VIOLATION FOR EACH DAY THAT THE ILLEGAL
18 GAMING ACTIVITY REMAINS ACCESSIBLE ON THE INTERNET WEBSITE TO PERSONS
19 PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE STATE.
20 (D) (1) THE RELIEF GRANTED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OR (B) OF THIS
21 SECTION AGAINST A FINANCIAL TRANSACTION PROVIDER OR OTHER PERSON THAT
22 SUPPORTS THE OPERATION, CONDUCT, OR PROMOTION OF ILLEGAL ONLINE
23 GAMBLING AND IS NOT OTHERWISE ENGAGED IN ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING SHALL:
24 (I) BE LIMITED TO THE SUSPENSION OF PROCESSING
25 TRANSACTIONS FOR THE ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING OPERATOR WITH PERSONS
26 PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE STATE;
27 (II) BE LIMITED TO CEASING SUPPORT OF THE OPERATION,
28 CONDUCT, OR PROMOTION OF ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING IN THE STATE; AND
29 (III) SPECIFY THE INTERNET WEBSITE TO WHICH IT APPLIES.
30 (2) (I) A VIOLATION OF AN ORDER ENTERED AGAINST A FINANCIAL
31 TRANSACTION PROVIDER OR OTHER PERSON THAT SUPPORTS THE OPERATION,
32 CONDUCT, OR PROMOTION OF ILLEGAL ONLINE GAMBLING IS PUNISHABLE BY A

