6 9–1F–11.
7 THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL MAY ENTER INTO AGREEMENTS
8 WITH THE COMMISSION OR ANY FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT
9 AGENCY FOR THE EXCHANGE AND RELEASE OF INVESTIGATORY AND OTHER
10 INFORMATION IF THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL DETERMINES THAT THE
11 RELEASE OF THE INFORMATION WILL BE CONSISTENT WITH THE POLICY OF THE
12 STATE AS REFLECTED IN THIS SUBTITLE.
13 9–1F–12.
14 THE COMMISSION MAY DENY, REVOKE, SUSPEND, CONDITION, OR LIMIT
15 LICENSES OR PERMITS ISSUED BY THE COMMISSION FOR FAILURE TO COMPLY WITH
16 THIS SUBTITLE.
17 9–1F–13.
18 A VIOLATION OF THIS SUBTITLE IS:
19 (1) AN UNFAIR, ABUSIVE, OR DECEPTIVE TRADE PRACTICE WITHIN
20 THE MEANING OF TITLE 13 OF THE COMMERCIAL LAW ARTICLE; AND
21 (2) SUBJECT TO THE ENFORCEMENT AND PENALTY PROVISIONS
22 CONTAINED IN TITLE 13 OF THE COMMERCIAL LAW ARTICLE.
23 9–1F–14.
24 THE DIVISION SHALL HAVE THE AUTHORITY TO ADOPT RULES, REGULATIONS,
25 AND STANDARDS TO FURTHER THE PURPOSES OF THIS SUBTITLE, INCLUDING THE
26 PREVENTION AND RESTRAINT OF THE CONDUCT AND OFFERING OF ILLEGAL ONLINE
27 GAMBLING TO PERSONS PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE STATE.
28 9–1F–15.

14 HOUSE BILL 1226
1 THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL, A PROSECUTING ATTORNEY, AND
2 THE COURT SHALL CONSTRUE LIBERALLY THIS SUBTITLE RELATING TO GAMBLING
3 AND BETTING TO PREVENT THE ACTIVITIES PROHIBITED.
4 9–1F–16.
5 THIS SUBTITLE MAY BE CITED AS THE MARYLAND ILLEGAL ONLINE
6 GAMBLING ENFORCEMENT ACT.
7 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
8 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
________________________________________________________________________________
Governor.
________________________________________________________________________________
Speaker of the House of Delegates.
________________________________________________________________________________
President of the Senate.

